The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Sept. 17: The broad-based Nifty of the National Stock Exchange crossed the 5000-mark to touch a high of 5003.05, a level not since May 23, 2008. The Nifty closed at 4965.55 points, a net gain of 7.15 points or 0.14 per cent. Analysts feel that the market will continue to rally after consolidating for the next few days at the current levels.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 17: The government today announced productivity-linked bonus for over 13 lakh railway employees. The bonus will be equivalent to 75 days of their wages in financial year 2008-09.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 17: The RBI has started the process of repo or ready forward in corporate bonds by releasing draft norms in this regard. Investors holding such a bond can now borrow funds by pledging them in a repurchase agreement with another entity.                             
	 Melbourne, Sept. 17: Vodafone Hutchison has announced offshoring a total of 450 call centre jobs from Melbourne to India and Tasmania. The company will transfer jobs to a call centre in Mumbai and Kingston.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 17: Luxembourg-based Millicom International Cellular has rejected BSNLs bid to acquire its Sri Lankan operations.                                                                                                                           
